## 4. Integration Objective

Google Cloud should power the application’s **AI document intelligence layer**.

### Primary responsibilities

| Responsibility | Description |
|---|---|
| Document description generation | create short, user-friendly summaries for document listings |
| Document summarization | produce concise admin-facing summaries |
| Metadata generation | suggest title, tags, categories, slugs, and SEO text |
| Document classification | infer type, purpose, audience, or suite placement |
| Structured content assistance | support future drafting and enrichment workflows |
| AI operations visibility | provide logging, observability, and access control |

### Core design principle

**The web application owns the workflow. Google Cloud owns the AI execution environment.**

That means the application remains the source of truth for:

- who requested the generation
- what document is being processed
- what result was accepted or edited
- how the result is stored in Firestore

Google Cloud provides the managed model execution and supporting cloud services needed to make the AI subsystem reliable and secure.

