## 13. Model Strategy

The current code uses `gemini-2.5-flash`, which is sensible for short document descriptions.

### Recommended model roles

| Model role | Recommended class |
|---|---|
| document descriptions | Gemini Flash |
| metadata generation | Gemini Flash |
| classification | Gemini Flash |
| richer summaries or complex synthesis | Gemini Pro or higher-capability model if needed |

### Important rule

Do not hardcode the model permanently in source code for all environments.

Instead, use environment-based configuration such as:

- `AI_DESCRIPTION_MODEL`
- `AI_SUMMARY_MODEL`
- `AI_METADATA_MODEL`

### Why

- easier rollback
- easier environment-specific tuning
- easier cost control
- cleaner experimentation

