## 14. Recommended Application Changes

The current app works, but it needs more structure around the AI layer.

## 14.1 Replace hardcoded model configuration

Move model selection from source code into configuration.

### Current pattern

`src/ai/genkit.ts` uses a hardcoded default model.

### Recommended target

Read the model from environment configuration and support separate model assignments per task.

## 14.2 Add feature flags

Recommended flags:

- `AI_GENERATION_ENABLED`
- `AI_DOCUMENT_DESCRIPTION_ENABLED`
- `AI_DOCUMENT_SUMMARY_ENABLED`
- `AI_METADATA_SUGGESTION_ENABLED`
- `AI_CLASSIFICATION_ENABLED`

### Why

If Gemini or Vertex AI has issues, the rest of the application should continue operating with manual admin input.

## 14.3 Add an AI orchestration service layer

Create a dedicated application service such as:

- `src/lib/ai-service.ts`
- `src/lib/ai-document-input.ts`
- `src/lib/ai-logging.ts`

### Responsibilities

- validate inputs
- normalize documents
- call AI gateway or Genkit flow
- return typed responses
- log usage
- apply feature flags

## 14.4 Add AI request persistence

Before generation, create a Firestore record such as `ai_generation_jobs`.

### Why

- better traceability
- operational debugging
- future async processing support

