## 22. Error Handling and Fallback Design

The AI layer must fail in a controlled way.

## 22.1 Likely failure modes

| Failure mode | Required handling |
|---|---|
| invalid input | return validation error immediately |
| unsupported MIME type | reject cleanly |
| oversize file | reject or route to staged processing |
| model timeout | return retry-safe failure |
| Vertex AI auth error | log and surface operational alert |
| quota issue | log and provide fallback/manual option |
| empty model response | treat as failure, not success |
| gateway unavailable | manual admin entry remains available |

## 22.2 Fallback rule

If AI generation fails, the document workflow must remain usable.

That means:

- the admin form stays editable
- manual entry remains available
- the failed request is logged
- repeated failures trigger operational review

