## 28. Final Operating Model

When implemented properly, the Google Cloud integration should operate like this:

- the **web application** owns the document workflow and admin review experience
- **Firebase / Firestore** remain the platform’s source of truth for document metadata and generation records
- **Google Cloud** hosts the AI execution boundary
- **Vertex AI Gemini** performs the actual inference work
- **Cloud Run** isolates the AI logic from the main app runtime
- **Secret Manager** protects credentials and configuration
- **IAM** controls what can call what
- **Cloud Logging and Monitoring** provide operational visibility
- **Cloud Storage** can support larger or staged file workflows when needed

That is the intended production model.

The current app already proves the feature concept. Google Cloud is what turns that concept into a controlled, supportable, production-grade subsystem instead of a clever button with trust issues.


